{"model": "Mistral Small 3.2 24B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_combinatorics__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 73, "generation_tokens": 344, "prompt_tps": 124.64805255748476, "generation_tps": 33.14857819099151, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 10.65766724999412, "output": "To determine the number of ways to choose 3 items from a set of 7, we can use the combination formula. The combination formula is given by:\n\nC(n, k) = n! / (k! * (n - k)!)\n\nWhere:\n- n is the total number of items.\n- k is the number of items to choose.\n- \"!\" denotes factorial, which is the product of all positive integers up to that number.\n\nStep-by-step calculation:\n\n1. Identify the values of n and k:\n   - n = 7 (total items)\n   - k = 3 (items to choose)\n\n2. Plug the values into the combination formula:\n   C(7, 3) = 7! / (3! * (7 - 3)!)\n   C(7, 3) = 7! / (3! * 4!)\n\n3. Calculate the factorials:\n   - 7! = 7 \u00d7 6 \u00d7 5 \u00d7 4 \u00d7 3 \u00d7 2 \u00d7 1 = 5040\n   - 3! = 3 \u00d7 2 \u00d7 1 = 6\n   - 4! = 4 \u00d7 3 \u00d7 2 \u00d7 1 = 24\n\n4. Substitute the factorial values back into the formula:\n   C(7, 3) = 5040 / (6 * 24)\n   C(7, 3) = 5040 / 144\n\n5. Perform the division:\n   C(7, 3) = 35\n\nANSWER: 35</s>", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "0906c375ac54"}
